  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2006-03-28",
    "date": "2006-05-03T19:12:35Z",
    "text": "Stop Tuberculosis (TB) Now Act of 2006 - Amends the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961 to require (currently, authorizes) the President to furnish assistance for tuberculosis (TB) prevention, treatment, and elimination.\n\nGives priority to activities described in the Stop TB Strategy (as defined by this Act). Revises related fund use provisions.\n\nAuthorizes the President, through the United States Agency for International Development (USAID), to provide increased resources to the World Health Organization (WHO) and the Stop Tuberculosis Partnership to improve the capacity of countries with high TB rates and other affected countries to implement the Stop TB Strategy.\n\nAuthorizes appropriations for Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDCP) TB activities."
  },
